'''Bruno Messerli''' (born September 17, 1931 in Belp) is a [[Swiss]] [[geographer]] and [[university professor]], who focuses on geographic high mountain research.<ref name="Bio One">{{cite web|title=Mountain Research and Development|url=http://www.bioone.org/doi/full/10.1659/0276-4741%282002%29022%5B0080%3ARDBPBM%5D2.0.CO%3B2|publisher=Bio One|accessdate=5 February 2018}}</ref> He was appointed Full Professor of [[Geomorphology]] in 1968 by the [[University of Bern]]<ref name="Institute of Geography">{{cite web|title=Institute of Geography|url=http://www.geography.unibe.ch/about_us/staff/emeriti/prof_em_dr_messerli_bruno/index_eng.html|publisher=Institute of Geography|accessdate=5 February 2018}}</ref>, where he worked in teaching and research until his retirement in 1996.<ref name="King Albert">{{cite web|title=ALBERT MOUNTAIN AWARDS|url=http://www.king-albert.ch/award-winners/56-bruno-messerli|publisher=King Albert|accessdate=5 February 2018}}</ref> He contributed significantly to the inclusion of a mountain chapter in the [[Agenda 21]].<ref name="Global 500 Environmental Forum">{{cite web|title=Dr. Bruno Messerli, Universitat Bern|url=https://archive.is/20130824114958/http://www.global500.org/Roll-of-Honour-/-Laureate-Database/Dr.-Bruno-Messerli.html|publisher=Global 500 Environmental Forum|accessdate=5 February 2018}}</ref>
==Awards== *1988: Global 500 Award of the United Nations Environment Program (UNEP)<ref name="King Albert" /> *1990: [[Marcel Benoist Prize]] *2002: Gold medal of King Albert I Memorial Foundation <ref name="Lefigaro">{{cite web|title=Lorenz Bäumer dans une nouvelle dimension|url=http://madame.lefigaro.fr/style/lorenz-baeumer-dans-nouvelle-dimension-100613-386004|publisher=Lefigaro|accessdate=5 February 2018}}</ref> *2002: [[Gold Medal (RGS)|Gold Medal]] ( Founder's Medal ) of the Royal Geographical Society *2002: FAO - Medal for the UN - International Year of Mountains, Global Mountain Summit in Bishkek, Kyrghyzstan
==Works== *with H. Oeschger and M. Svilar (ed.): ''The climate. Analyzes and models, history and future'' . Springer Verlag, 1980. *with JD Ives (ed.): ''Mountain Ecosystems, Stability and Instability'' . Spec. Publ. IGU Congress Paris - Alps 1984. Mountain Research and Development *with E. Brugger, G. Furrer and P. Messerli (ed.): ''Upheaval in the mountain area. The development of the Swiss mountain area between independence and dependence from an economic and ecological point of view'' . Main publishing house, Berne 1984. *with JD Ives: ''The Himalayan dilemma. Reconciling Development and Conservation'' . UNU / Routledge, London / New York 1989, {{ISBN|0-415-01157-4}} . *with JD Ives (ed.): Mountains of the World. A Global Priority . Parthenon, Carnforth / New York 1997, {{ISBN|1-85070-781-2}} . *with T. Hofer: ''Floods in Bangladesh. History, Dynamics and Rethinking the Role of the Himalayas'' . United Nations University Press, Tokyo / New York 2006.
