'''Lower Guinea''' may refer to: * [[Maritime Guinea]], the coastal region of the republic of [[Guinea]].<ref>[http://www.britannica.com/place/Guinea "Guinea"]. britannica.com. Accessed 2 October 2015</ref> * in [[biogeography]], a region of coastal tropical forests stretching along the [[Gulf of Guinea]], from [[Ghana]] through [[Benin]], [[Togo]], [[Nigeria]], and [[Cameroon]]. It is separated from [[Upper Guinea]] by the drier [[Dahomey Gap]].<ref>"Guinean Forests of West Africa." Conservation International. Accessed 2 October 2015. [http://www.cepf.net/resources/hotspots/africa/Pages/Guinean-Forests-of-West-Africa.aspx]</ref>
