{{coord missing|Namibia}}

The '''Mayuni Conservancy''' is a conservation area in [[Linyanti Constituency]], in [[Namibia]]'s northeastern [[Caprivi Region]], along the eastern bank of the [[Cuando River]].<ref>{{cite book
|last=Shapi
|first=Martin
|title=Mayuni Conservancy socio-economic and livelihood approaches, with respect to contemporary natural resource conservation
|year=2003
|publisher=[[University of Namibia]]. Multidisciplinary Research and Consultancy Centre
|location=Windhoek
|url=https://books.google.com/?id=Urm2AAAAIAAJ&q=%22Mayuni+Conservancy%22&dq=%22Mayuni+Conservancy%22}}</ref>

==Facilities==
Nambwa Campsite is in the Mayuni conservation area and started its operations in the year 2004. Nambwa is in the [[Kongola]] area in the [[Caprivi region]]. The campsite is located on the west of [[Katima Mulilo]] along the [[Katima Mulilo]] Highway, on the peripherals of the [[Bwabwata National Park]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.overlandingafrica.com/maps/namibia/kwando-river/ |title=Map of Kwando River, Namibia - Kwando River Map Africa |publisher=Overlandingafrica.com |date= |accessdate=2012-10-14}}</ref><ref>http://baobabguides.com/2010/05/10/nambwa-community-campsite-caprivi-namibia/ Baobabguides.com</ref><ref>[http://www.namibweb.com/nambwacamp.htm Nambwa Camp] at Namibweb.com</ref><ref>[http://www.namibian.org/travel/community/nambwa.html Nambwa] at Namibian.org</ref>

