{{Unreferenced|date=April 2018}}
'''Palestine Summer Time''' is the practice in the [[State of Palestine]] by which clocks are advanced by one hour.

The Palestinian Territories operate on "Palestinian Standard Time", which observes Daylight Saving Time (DST) at slightly different times. This has led to some confusion. In the [[State of Palestine]], DST ends later, which can lead to some confusion.

